-or-spi","target":"sh1106-1p3-inch-oled-128x64-display-module-runs-on-3v3-or-5v-via-i2c-or-spi","line":98},{"title":"bno055-9dof-absolute-orientation-imu-with-sensor-fusion-i2c","target":"bno055-9dof-absolute-orientation-imu-with-sensor-fusion-i2c","line":99},{"title":"ina219-high-side-current-sensor-26v-i2c-for-power-monitoring","target":"ina219-high-side-current-sensor-26v-i2c-for-power-monitoring","line":100},{"title":"dht11-temperature-humidity-sensor-single-wire-0-50c","target":"dht11-temperature-humidity-sensor-single-wire-0-50c","line":101},{"title":"microcontrollers","target":"microcontrollers","line":104},{"title":"communication","target":"communication","line":105}],"metadata":{"description":"Pre-configured ESP8266 IoT board from SparkFun — ships with Blynk firmware for quick phone-to-hardware projects. Limited GPIO exposure, best for WiFi-connected sensor/actuator nodes that talk to a phone app","topics":["[[microcontrollers]]","[[communication]]"],"status":"needs-test","quantity":2,"voltage":[3.3],"interfaces":["GPIO","I2C","SPI","UART","WiFi","USB"],"logic_level":"3.3V","manufacturer":"SparkFun","mcu":"ESP8266 (ESP-12S module)","clock_mhz":80,"flash_kb":4096,"sram_kb":80,"part_number":"DEV-13794","pinout":"GPIO0  — user button (active LOW), boot mode\nGPIO2  — onboard LED\nGPIO4  — I2C SDA\nGPIO5  — I2C SCL\nGPIO12 — available (active-low LED on some revisions)\nGPIO13 — available\nGPIO14 — available\nGPIO15 — boot mode (must be LOW at boot)\nGPIO16 — wake from deep sleep\nADC    — analog input (0-1V)\n3V3    — 3.3V output\nGND    — ground\nVBAT   — battery input (3.3-6V, onboard LiPo charger)\n5V     — USB 5V\n","compatible_with":["[[esp8266-nodemcu-amica-is-a-wifi-mcu-with-11-io-at-3v3]]","[[nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3]]","[[sh1106-1p3-inch-oled-128x64-display-module-runs-on-3v3-or-5v-via-i2c-or-spi]]","[[bno055-9dof-absolute-orientation-imu-with-sensor-fusion-i2c]]","[[ina219-high-side-current-sensor-26v-i2c-for-power-monitoring]]","[[dht11-temperature-humidity-sensor-single-wire-0-50c]]"],"level_shifter_needed":["[[arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b]]","[[arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts]]"],"used_in":[],"warnings":["3.3V logic — 5V on ANY pin will damage the ESP8266","Limited GPIO breakout compared to NodeMCU boards — check which pins are exposed on your revision","Blynk legacy cloud service has been discontinued — board still works with custom firmware","Same ESP8266 boot pin restrictions as NodeMCU (GPIO0, GPIO2, GPIO15)"],"datasheet_url":"https://www.sparkfun.com/products/13794"},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"docs/parts/sparkfun-blynk-board-esp8266-wifi-iot-preconfigured.md"},"smart_blocks:docs/parts/sparkfun-blynk-board-esp8266-wifi-iot-preconfigured.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"11q2mj5","at":1776210587400},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.03651348,-0.02574059,0.06020952,-0.05187446,0.00363771,-0.01555255,-0.03232832,0.06585584,-0.05645131,-0.01117742,-0.0374475,-0.07075449,0.04234447,0.02049402,0.03058976,0.00186135,0.0496135,-0.09729996,-0.04647543,0.04782953,0.08386334,-0.085221,-0.00929328,-0.04187568,0.03727106,0.03270433,0.03826345,-0.04297034,-0.03912475,-0.20477703,0.03097577,-0.01369786,0.03187289,0.01967892,-0.04684599,-0.08013602,-0.07346534,0.0061403,-0.09016889,-0.00608013,0.04457398,0.0174408,-0.0536178,0.00385585,-0.01016816,-0.03014954,0.03738982,-0.01779164,0.02688547,-0.07559481,0.01189846,-0.034764,0.02974053,-0.04149855,0.04511162,0.0255512,-0.00427045,0.04264925,0.0506435,-0.03297629,0.04783141,0.08885495,-0.19378535,0.12248764,0.01913958,0.04667545,-0.02001499,-0.08284403,0.09814998,-0.00697239,-0.06616317,-0.00158441,0.02060891,0.02564043,-0.0091602,0.03926675,-0.0132163,-0.00926094,0.00497307,-0.0247393,-0.03674444,0.02803104,-0.0126928,0.04051399,0.01167362,-0.00014368,0.02439808,-0.00799507,0.00818402,0.04751818,-0.03485437,